The '''C-NCAP''' (Chinese: 中国新车评价规程) is a Chinese [[car safety]] assessment program. It is primarily modeled after safety standards established by [[Euro NCAP]]<ref>http://safety.trw.com/how-c-ncap-and-chinas-passive-safety-regulations-will-catch-up-with-europe-by-2018/1205/</ref> and is run by the China Automotive Technology and Research Center.<ref>http://www.catarc.ac.cn/ac_en/content/20071228/7488.html</ref>

