{{Infobox person | image = | image_size = | name = Otávio Azevedo | caption = | birth_name = Otávio Marques de Azevedo | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | restingplace = | nationality = Brazilian | religion = | ethnicity = | residence = | education = | alma mater = [[Pontifícia Universidade Católica de Minas Gerais]] | occupation = CEO, [[Andrade Gutierrez]] | known for = | salary = | networth = | spouse = | parents = | children = | relatives = | website = }}
'''Otávio Marques de Azevedo''' is a Brazilian businessman, the CEO of [[Andrade Gutierrez]], a Brazilian conglomerate.
Azevedo received a bachelor's degree in Electrical Engineering from [[Pontifícia Universidade Católica de Minas Gerais]].<ref name=Bloomberg>{{cite web|title=Executive Profile: Otavio Marques de Azevedo|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=10822121&privcapId=142377579|website=Bloomberg|accessdate=19 June 2015}}</ref>
In June 2015, he was arrested as part of a major investigation into corruption at the state-owned oil company [[Petrobras]].<ref name=BBC>{{cite news|title=Petrobras scandal: Top construction bosses arrested in Brazil|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-33203790|accessdate=19 June 2015|work=BBC|date=19 June 2015}}</ref>
