{{Infobox person |name=Wayne Pai |parents= |native_name = 白文正 |birth_name = Pai Wen-cheng |birth_date={{birth date|1952|10|14|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Penghu]], [[Taiwan]] |death_date= {{death date and age|df=y|2008|7|2|1952|10|14}} |death_place = [[Penghu]], [[Taiwan]] |alma_mater=[[National Chiao Tung University]] |children = 3 |spouse=魏明春 |occupation=businessman |relatives = 白介宇 (son) }}
'''Wayne Pai''' ({{zh|c=白文正|p=Pai Wencheng}}; 14 October 1952 – July 2008) was a [[Taiwan]]ese [[businessman]].
Pai founded the Polaris Group (寶來集團), the second largest securities brokerage of Taiwan,<ref name="CNA">[http://times.hinet.net/times/article.do?newsid=1606209&option=english Polaris Group head commits suicide in Penghu], ''Central News Agency'', July 4, 2008.</ref> and served as the chairman of the company. Pai was considered a successful businessperson,<ref>{{zh icon}}[http://www.libertytimes.com.tw/2005/new/mar/20/today-stock5.htm 證金業急先鋒白文正一頁傳奇史], ''Liberty Times'', March 20, 2005.</ref> but was entangled in multiple scandals prior to his death.<ref>{{zh icon}}[http://news.yam.com/view/mkmnews.php/602344 形象精明一世的白文正摔了一大跤], ''Wealth'' (''財訊''), May 8, 2008.</ref> He disappeared in [[Penghu]] since 2 July 2008. The police found Pai's body and confirmed his death by suicide on the morning of 4 July 2008.<ref name="CNA"/>
